HEADWORD: Coversed sine
<hw>Co*versed" sine</hw> <pr>(k?-v?rst" s?n`)</pr>. <ety>[<ets>Co-</ets>
(=<ets>co-</ets> in <ets>co-</ets> sine) + <ets>versed
sine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>The versed sine of the
complement of an arc or angle. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Functions</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
